reviews.review_text: I had the chance to try an amazing Nigerian dish that left a lasting impression. The rice and beans were cooked to perfection, with a delightful smoky and spicy flavor. The oxtail stew, slow-cooked with a variety of vegetables, added a wonderful texture and taste. The oxtail itself was incredibly tender, practically melting in my mouth. The meal was rounded out with a refreshing cabbage salad and a warm, sweet cornbread. It was a truly satisfying and hearty meal that I would highly recommend to anyone curious about Nigerian cuisine.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Fabricio, Thank you for taking the time to give us such great ratings about your food, means a lot and we appreciate your business. Hope to see you again soon!

reviews.review_text: Pre-ordered the Christmas package via Uber Eats on the 23rd to arrive at my apartment at 24th at 8. Received the order promptly on the 24th. I couldn t even help myself, I just started eating because the food smelled so good. It tastes amazing 20/10 on presentation and taste. And the  Christmas present  was a nice touch as well. The candle smells divine. Will definitely be ordering in the future as well as recommending to everyone I know. Good Job Vansuya, keep up the good work.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your review, we are glad to hear you loved our food. Thanks for your business means a lot to us, we hope to see you soon again.

reviews.review_text: Absolutely delicious! I ll admit, I had no idea what to expect because I ve never had Nigerian food before. I ordered the Egusi Soup with  wrap  and Naija Smokey Jollof Rice. The Egusi soup was incredible - rich in spices, with cubes of beef. The beef was a little tough for my preference but with all the yummy flavour and texture going on, I still ate two servings. The  wrap  that came with it was more like a ball of sticky semolina-like grain to eat the soup with, and it soaks up all those curried spices nicely. The rice with the smokey chicken was also really good! Very cool. I look forward to trying more Nigerian food in the future :)
Loved the chicken Suya!! (or Agashi as we call it in Sudan).

Very delicious and tasty jollof rice with the right amount of spice, not soggy or soft which is a plus. The smoky flavour makes it even better. The chicken is well cooked. A perfect example of Nigerian Jollof rice and chicken.

Their meals are provide an authentic window into Nigerian culture. From suya to jollof rice to zobo...Each dish brings to mind the beauty and tastiness of Nigerian cuisine. Finally, their customer service is unrivalled. One of the best out here. Try it for yourself!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your review, we are glad to hear you loved our food. Thanks for your business. We will keep bringing home close to you

reviews.review_text: This is my first time trying this place and also at a shared takeout location. This building is shared by 9 different take out only restaurants and you have to call them to bring out your order. There is free parking all along the street. I ordered the chicken shawarma through UberEats. The restaurant tried to reach me to tell me they ran out of chicken so some of it will be beef. I did receive a call but the caller ID automatically said suspected spam so I didnt answer. They were nice to write me a note with my order to let me know some things were changed. I did get to try both chicken and beef tough. The chicken was soft but the beef to me was a lot tougher. I prefer the chicken so I will try the chicken only again next time. I am a very big fan of sauce and if you like it too, this is a great place for you. The wrap is smothered in sauce and filled with meet and cabbage. If you cannot tolerate spice, the mild would still have a little spice as well. The large version was bigger than a shawarma wrap at other places. However, I found the original price very expensive as it was around $18 for a large wrap. The UberEats BOGO was a very good deal though.

I REALLY love the food but the portion sizes for Egusi are incredibly small and it s close to 40$ to order some on Uber. 40$ for a bowl 1/3 full is really upsetting. If the portion was a bit bigger, or if the value was better, I d eat here maybe once a week! Deserves a 5 star for flavour but not cost,
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Sina, Thank you for taking the time to give us such great ratings about your food, ubereats takes over 30% fee on all orders why our prices are high, because we have to factor that in, but your feedback means a lot and we appreciate your business. Hope to see you again soon!

reviews.review_text: the food and portions are great, slightly expensive but understandably so. I would love if you were able to order and get deliveries through doordash though (please get on doordash  )

We are on doordash too. Hope to see you again soon!

reviews.review_text: I was glad to find easy access to Nigerian food in Vancity. The jollof rice couldn t be more smoky! The shawarma was indeed spicy and Nigerian. And it was massive!  I d say to watch for the spiciness though .the mild wasn t really mild.

Friend gave me some food from here. A tad on the spicey side for one item. The fried rice and plantain was tasty along with the bbq turkey. The chicken however was quite spicey. The prices I saw for the uber ests order were a  it much as well. 20$ for fried rice... without any protein...
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Andrew, Thanks for your feedback and we are glad you loved our food and sorry about the spice (Nigerian foods are typically spicy). Our fried rice gives you an option to pick your protein, unfortunately because all proteins that come with the fried rice are the not the same price hence ubereats let s us set it up that way (having a fixed price and then you have option to pick which protein you want) We look forward to having you again. Happy New year and have a great week ahead.

reviews.review_text: Best African food in Vancouver! Removed a star because of the spicy shawarma. My friends and i got really sick the day after eating it and i had terrible diarrhea. I think they over did the spice that day. I had to drink two venti cups of warm milk to feel a bit of relief. This includes my Yoruba friends who can take spice. So i guess it was just a bad batch. I guess if you cant handle spicy/really hot food. Then ask them to make it as mild as possible.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Unknown, we wish your name wasn t mysterious so we could make it up to you. Yes we are sorry about the spicy level, we cook our recipes as if this was back home. We have you come by again soon ! Thank you once again ! We appreciate your feedback

reviews.review_text: Good food , a little pricey because you can only order online through skip or uber, which I found out the hard way.

reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your review, we are glad to hear you loved our food. Thanks for your business.

reviews.review_text: I ordered pickup, through Uber Eats. Got 2 chicken shawarma wraps. The food runner was friendly upon pickup. The wraps were huge! However, I found the wraps to be of birthing but cabbage, tons of mayo, and a hotdog in the middle. I had ordered chicken shawarma, and paid for the extra chicken. But there was not chicken. Or maybe, it is just me? Is this common with Nigerian food? I found the wrap difficult to eat because of the excess mayo/sauce.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Win, thanks for your review. Nigerian chicken shawarma is juicy and made with shredded chicken, cabbage, carrot, mayo, ketchup and chicken sausage. It isn t delicious if it isn t juicy. We also take instructions from customer who request for little sauce on it. We are sorry if we didn t meet your expectations

reviews.review_text: Jollof rice taste amazing..but omg, the egusi soup looks like egg sauce and  taste so awful.. Please improve on the taste and looks of your egusi soup Thank you

So today, First i was expectin so much from the jollof rice cos I tried the African jollof rice in calgary and it was good so i was xpectin same here but honestly it was not so good to my taste. Ordered the puff puff balls too cos i had one last week three times at my friends place who said she ordered from this company but suprisely when I ordered today the taste was so different from the one i had tried. I had to throw it away. U guys should be consistent please. The price are so much for the food to be a mess.

Dont order pickup.  Its such a hassle.  Theres no number to call for pickup on the outside of the building and no estimated time on when your food will be ready.  The food is amazing but getting it almost doesnt seem worth it unless you pay exorbitant skip or uber prices on top
They have the most blandest tasteless Jollof rice I have ever had in my life. Shawarma was great.

The jollof rice and fried rice seasoning isn t the best, i don t know why but not my favourite. Also I think the quality of the suya has changed.. it s not as spicy anymore (the Wakanda version).   Nigerian suya is known for its spicy delicacy. Hoping things get improved!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your review, we are sorry to hear you didnt like your meal, we will like to make it up to you and make you happy. Looking forward to your next order.

reviews.review_text: Ordered the  party tray  jollof for a party supposed to be 6L not even 2L of rice they gave us. couldn t even feed 3 people if we wanted to, terrible portion size and a straight up scam. nearly 180 dollars for rice that can t even feed 3 people? chai. Taking advantage of the fact that they are the only nigerian restaurant and have become very stingy i do NOT recommend. the chicken they gave us was still clucking undercooked and bloody. i never see nonsense like this one in my life o. my fellow nigerians, AVOID!! this isn t the first time o, fame don get into they head abeg too overpriced!! Can you believe nonsense. i m calling health and safety to come and inspect this place before someone gets really sick.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: So sorry about this, we take full responsibility, although we do carry out temp check for every protein grilled or fried, this must have been an oversight on one of the pieces of chicken gotten. About the servings we do have a measurement for each meals and will never give a customer less, we are known for our portions and will continue to serve customers the best meals. Thanks for your feedback, as we are learning everyday to serve our customers better

reviews.review_text: Service used to be consistent, you no longer know what you will get. Prices have doubled up within the past one year, promos on Uber eat are fraudulent. Like today , I saw a jollof + turkey order for 23dollar with a promo to add chicken for 9 dollar. The food came with chicken and no turkey displayed in the picture. I will be sending Uber eat an official complaint the next time this occur.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for your feedback, we are all aware of the inflation and how cost of food supplies have gone up more than 100%, to survive as a business we have to increase prices too. We also get charged 30% for every order that comes through ubereats, we are sure you are not aware of that and we have to factor that into our prices. As regards to the promo on the app but we don t control the Ubereats app, we are just a platform there- you might want to pass that feedback to them. We can see from the image you posted that you ordered BBQ Chicken and we can see thats what you got, we do not understand what the problem is? Giving a business 1 star review when we clearly didnt do anything wrong is not fair! Feel free to share your feedback with uber, but as a company we are very transparent and pride ourselves in delivering great services to our customers.

reviews.review_text: I love the dark bits in paella, and I have had amazing Jollof rices before. Having said that the Jollof rice here was disappointing. It looked great but the taste was nothing but burnt. I could not taste anything else. I imagine they over-burnt the rice and saved the bits on top hoping it would be okay, it was not. Hopefully I was just an extremely unlucky case.

Ordered fried rice with chicken suya via UberEats, and all I got was a box of fried rice, no protein in sight. The rice itself was good but thats not the meal I ordered, and thats a lot of money for just rice...
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello Adrien, We are sincerely sorry about that, we will make this doesn t repeat itself. Hope you enjoy your meal. Have a great day
